Description: Neck sherd of Milesian Fikellura pottery oinochoe; interior reserved; exterior, white slip; from top: part of dividing band consisting of painted dot and billet pattern; triple cable (with added red on three dots in file); black band at junction with shoulder.
Curator's comments: For the triple cable (with added red on the dots) on the neck of an amphora, compare British Museum 1949,0516.1 (CVA BM 8, pl. 8, 3, dated about 530 BC; New York group).
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GF.144)
